2024-10-31, **Disentangling data contributions to the precision measurement of the largest leptonic mixing angle**, P. T. Quyen et.al., [2410.23756v1](http://arxiv.org/abs/2410.23756v1)

 Leptonic mixing, together with the massiveness of neutrinos, is one of the most significant discoveries in contemporary particle physics. The observed differences in the mixing patterns of quarks and leptons may shed light on our understanding of the three-generation structure of the Standard Model. This study examines the precise measurement of the largest leptonic mixing angle $	heta\_{23}$ through the analysis of neutrino oscillation data samples. Our findings indicate that, contrary to common understanding, the ${
